cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use AlphaFold Sovereign MCP in research, please cite it
  using the metadata below. For citations of specific data sources
  accessed through this software (AlphaFold DB, UniProt, etc.)
  please also cite those sources according to their own citation
  requirements.
type: software
title: "AlphaFold Sovereign MCP"
abstract: >-
  A production-grade Model Context Protocol (MCP) server for
  sovereign structural-biology analysis. Provides 25+ tools spanning
  AlphaFold structure retrieval, persistent-homology topological data
  analysis, disease-ontology integration (MONDO, HPO, ICD-10/11,
  OMIM, Orphanet, Open Targets), variant triage (AlphaMissense,
  ClinVar, gnomAD), sequence-of-concern biosecurity screening, and
  federated multi-instance operation. Designed for pharmaceutical,
  clinical-research, and national-security deployments requiring
  air-gap installability, 21 CFR Part 11 audit trails, and
  FIPS 140-3 cryptographic compliance.
